1 /************************************************************************
2 *
3 * Device : RX/RX600/RX621,RX62N
4 *
5 * File Name : iodefine.h
6 *
7 * Abstract : Definition of I/O Register.
8 *
9 * History : 1.00 (2010-02-18) [Hardware Manual Revision : 0.5]
10 * : 1.01 (2010-04-21) [Hardware Manual Revision : 0.5]
11 * : 1.2 (2010-08-21) [Hardware Manual Revision : 1.0]
12 * : 1.3B (2012-06-17) [Hardware Manual Revision : 1.30]
13 * : 1.3C (2012-07-05) [Hardware Manual Revision : 1.30]
14 *
15 * NOTE : THIS IS A TYPICAL EXAMPLE.
16 *
17 * Copyright (C) 2012(2010) Renesas Electronics Corporation and
18 * Renesas Solutions Corp. All rights reserved.
19 *
20 ************************************************************************/
21 /********************************************************************************/
22 /* */
23 /* DESCRIPTION : Definition of ICU Register */
24 /* CPU TYPE : RX62N */
25 /* */
26 /* Usage : IR,DTCER,IER,IPR of ICU Register */
27 /* The following IR, DTCE, IEN, IPR macro functions simplify usage. */
28 /* The bit access operation is "Bit_Name(interrupt source,name)". */
29 /* A part of the name can be omitted. */
30 /* for example : */
31 /* IR(MTU0,TGIA0) = 0; expands to : */
32 /* ICU.IR[114].BIT.IR = 0; */
33 /* */
34 /* DTCE(ICU,IRQ0) = 1; expands to : */
35 /* ICU.DTCER[64].BIT.DTCE = 1; */
36 /* */
37 /* IEN(CMT0,CMI0) = 1; expands to : */
38 /* ICU.IER[0x03].BIT.IEN4 = 1; */
39 /* */
40 /* IPR(MTU1,TGIA1) = 2; expands to : */
41 /* IPR(MTU1,TGI ) = 2; // TGIA1,TGIB1 share IPR level. */
42 /* ICU.IPR[0x53].BIT.IPR = 2; */
43 /* */
44 /* IPR(SCI0,ERI0) = 3; expands to : */
45 /* IPR(SCI0, ) = 3; // SCI0 uses single IPR for all sources. */
46 /* ICU.IPR[0x80].BIT.IPR = 3; */
47 /* */
48 /* Usage : #pragma interrupt Function_Identifier(vect=**) */
49 /* The number of vector is "(interrupt source, name)". */
50 /* for example : */
51 /* #pragma interrupt INT_IRQ0(vect=VECT(ICU,IRQ0)) expands to : */
52 /* #pragma interrupt INT_IRQ0(vect=64) */
53 /* #pragma interrupt INT_CMT0_CMI0(vect=VECT(CMT0,CMI0)) expands to : */
54 /* #pragma interrupt INT_CMT0_CMI0(vect=28) */
55 /* #pragma interrupt INT_MTU0_TGIA0(vect=VECT(MTU0,TGIA0)) expands to : */
56 /* #pragma interrupt INT_MTU0_TGIA0(vect=114) */
57 /* */
58 /* Usage : MSTPCRA,MSTPCRB,MSTPCRC of SYSTEM Register */
59 /* The bit access operation is "MSTP(name)". */
60 /* The name that can be used is a macro name defined with "iodefine.h". */
61 /* for example : */
62 /* MSTP(TMR2) = 0; // TMR2,TMR3,TMR23 expands to : */
63 /* SYSTEM.MSTPCRA.BIT.MSTPA4 = 0; */
64 /* MSTP(SCI0) = 0; // SCI0,SMCI0 expands to : */
65 /* SYSTEM.MSTPCRB.BIT.MSTPB31 = 0; */
66 /* MSTP(MTU4) = 0; // MTUA,MTU0,MTU1,MTU2,MTU3,MTU4,MTU5 expands to : */
67 /* SYSTEM.MSTPCRA.BIT.MSTPA9 = 0; */
68 /* MSTP(CMT3) = 0; // CMT2,CMT3 expands to : */
69 /* SYSTEM.MSTPCRA.BIT.MSTPA14 = 0; */
70 /* */
71 /* */
72 /********************************************************************************/
